<paragraph blockId="2.[132,681,568,816]" pageId="2" pageNumber="83">
<emphasis box="[132,340,568,592]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="83">
Discussão: 
<taxonomicName authority="Curletti &amp; Migliore, 2014" authorityName="Curletti &amp; Migliore" authorityYear="2014" box="[235,340,568,592]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Agrilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="83" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aegrotus" status="sp. nov.">A. aegrotus</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[346,423,568,591]" pageId="2" pageNumber="83" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
também pertence ao grupo de 
<taxonomicName authority="Curletti &amp; Migliore, 2014" authorityName="Curletti &amp; Migliore" authorityYear="2014" box="[197,316,600,624]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Agrilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="83" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="timorosus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[197,316,600,624]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="83">A. timorosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[324,401,600,623]" pageId="2" pageNumber="83" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
Todavia, devido às suas pequenas dimensões (menos de 
<quantity box="[426,488,632,656]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="83" unit="mm" value="5.0">5 mm</quantity>
) na fauna brasileira pode ser comparado a 
<taxonomicName authority="Kerremans, 1897" authorityName="Kerremans" authorityYear="1897" box="[374,681,664,688]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Agrilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="83" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="villosulus">
<emphasis box="[374,493,664,688]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="83">A. villosulus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="KERREMANS, C." box="[503,681,664,688]" pageId="2" pageNumber="83" pagination="1 - 146" refId="ref15132" refString="KERREMANS, C. 1897. Contribution a l'etude de la faune intertropicale Americaine. Voyages de M. E. Gounelle au Bresil. Buprestides. Memoires de la Societe entomologique de Belgique, 6: 1 - 146." type="journal article" year="1897">Kerremans, 1897</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
descrito de 
<collectingRegion box="[243,369,696,720]" country="Brazil" name="Pernambuco" pageId="2" pageNumber="83">Pernambuco</collectingRegion>
e a 
<taxonomicName authority="Kerremans, 1897" authorityName="Kerremans" authorityYear="1897" box="[405,681,696,720]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Agrilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="83" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ignavus">
<emphasis box="[405,504,696,720]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="83">A. ignavus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="KERREMANS, C." box="[509,681,696,720]" pageId="2" pageNumber="83" pagination="1 - 146" refId="ref15132" refString="KERREMANS, C. 1897. Contribution a l'etude de la faune intertropicale Americaine. Voyages de M. E. Gounelle au Bresil. Buprestides. Memoires de la Societe entomologique de Belgique, 6: 1 - 146." type="journal article" year="1897">Kerremans, 1897</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
de 
<collectingRegion box="[161,222,728,752]" country="Brazil" name="Goias" pageId="2" pageNumber="83">Goiás</collectingRegion>
. O primeiro diferencia-se por possuir o pronoto mais alongado com os lados regularmente arredondados, o segundo por possuir a carena pré-umeral inteira.
</paragraph>
